 256:../VCOM-G1/GuitarPedal/eigen/Eigen/src/Core/PlainObjectBase.h ****       * product \a rows * \a cols, then no memory allocation is performed and
 257:../VCOM-G1/GuitarPedal/eigen/Eigen/src/Core/PlainObjectBase.h ****       * the current values are left unchanged. In all other cases, including
 258:../VCOM-G1/GuitarPedal/eigen/Eigen/src/Core/PlainObjectBase.h ****       * shrinking, the data is reallocated and all previous values are lost.
 259:../VCOM-G1/GuitarPedal/eigen/Eigen/src/Core/PlainObjectBase.h ****       *
 260:../VCOM-G1/GuitarPedal/eigen/Eigen/src/Core/PlainObjectBase.h ****       * Example: \include Matrix_resize_int_int.cpp
